     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "DyadForm[expr, {s1, s2, ...}] converts the operator expression expr to \
the form in terms of Dyad acting on the systems s1, s2, .... DyadForm[expr] \
do the same, but first extracts the list of systems from from expr. \
DyadForm[mat, {s1, s2, ...}] returns the operator expression in terms of Dyad \
corresponding to the matrix representation mat.", "synonyms" -> {}, 
